files.Summary: Represents an expression coming from query string. The scope determines at which depth in the to apply its expression.

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.AnyExpression
files.Summary: This expression tests if an attribute value equals any of the specified constants. It represents the "any" filter function, resulting from text such as: any(owner.name,'Jack','Joe','John') .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.ComparisonExpression
files.Summary: This expression compares two operands using a comparison operator. It represents comparison filter functions, resulting from text such as: equals(name,'Joe') , equals(owner,null) , or: greaterOrEqual(count(upVotes),count(downVotes),'1') .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.CountExpression
files.Summary: This expression determines the number of related resources in a to-many relationship. It represents the "count" function, resulting from text such as: count(articles) .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.FilterExpression
files.Summary: Represents the base type for filter functions that return a boolean value.

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.FunctionExpression
files.Summary: Represents the base type for functions that return a value.

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.HasExpression
files.Summary: This expression tests if a to-many relationship has related resources, optionally with a condition. It represents the "has" filter function, resulting from text such as: has(articles) , or: has(articles,equals(isHidden,'false')) .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.IdentifierExpression
files.Summary: Represents the base type for an identifier, such as a JSON:API attribute/relationship name, a constant value between quotes, or null.

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.IncludeElementExpression
files.Summary: Represents an element in an tree, resulting from text such as: articles.revisions .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.IncludeExpression
files.Summary: Represents an inclusion tree, resulting from text such as: owner,articles.revisions .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.IsTypeExpression
files.Summary: This expression tests if a resource in an inheritance hierarchy can be upcast to a derived type, optionally with a condition where the derived type is accessible. It represents the "isType" filter function, resulting from text such as: isType(,men) , isType(creator,men) , or: isType(creator,men,equals(hasBeard,'true')) .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.LiteralConstantExpression
files.Summary: Represents a non-null constant value, resulting from text such as: 'Jack', '123', or: 'true'.

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.LogicalExpression
files.Summary: This expression tests whether one or all of its boolean operands are true. It represents the logical AND/OR filter functions, resulting from text such as: and(equals(title,'Work'),has(articles)) , or: or(equals(title,'Work'),has(articles)) .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.MatchTextExpression
files.Summary: This expression allows partial matching on the value of a JSON:API attribute. It represents text-matching filter functions, resulting from text such as: startsWith(name,'The') , endsWith(name,'end.') , or: contains(name,'middle') .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.NotExpression
files.Summary: This expression tests for the logical negation of its operand. It represents the "not" filter function, resulting from text such as: not(equals(title,'Work')) .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.NullConstantExpression
files.Summary: Represents the constant null, resulting from the text: null.

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.PaginationElementQueryStringValueExpression
files.Summary: Represents an element in , resulting from text such as: 1, or: articles:2 .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.PaginationExpression
files.Summary: Represents a pagination, produced from .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.PaginationQueryStringValueExpression
files.Summary: Represents pagination in a query string, resulting from text such as: 1,articles:2 .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.QueryExpression
files.Summary: Represents the base data structure for immutable types that query string parameters are converted into. This intermediate structure is later transformed into System.Linq trees that are handled by Entity Framework Core.

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.QueryExpressionRewriter<TArgument>

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.QueryExpressionVisitor<TArgument, TResult>

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.QueryStringParameterScopeExpression
files.Summary: Represents the relationship scope of a query string parameter, resulting from text such as: ?sort[articles] , or: ?filter[author.articles.comments] .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.QueryableHandlerExpression
files.Summary: Holds an expression, used for custom query string handlers from s.

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.ResourceFieldChainExpression
files.Summary: Represents a chain of JSON:API fields (relationships and attributes), resulting from text such as: articles.revisions.author , or: owner.LastName .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.SortElementExpression
files.Summary: Represents an element in , resulting from text such as: lastName, -lastModifiedAt , or: count(children) .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.SortExpression
files.Summary: Represents a sorting, resulting from text such as: lastName,-lastModifiedAt,count(children) .

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.SparseFieldSetExpression

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.Expressions.SparseFieldTableExpression

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.FieldSelectors

files.Title: JsonApiDotNetCore.Queries.IEvaluatedIncludeCache
files.Summary: Provides in-memory storage for the evaluated inclusion tree within a request. This tree is produced from query string and resource definition callbacks. The cache enables the serialization layer to take changes from into account.
